The paper proposes a technique to accelerate the training phase of deep neural networks by reducing unnecessary computation and data access. This is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of optimization techniques. The paper specifically focuses on dropout, which is a regularization technique used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves developing a search algorithm, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves optimizing the use of GPUs, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
